## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-102">Eine Instanz von <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> wird erstellt, wenn <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> das <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> -Objekt oder `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` das-Objekt ein Ereignis auslöst.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> object raises an `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-103">Um Informationen zu einem `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` Ereignis zu erhalten, greifen Sie im-Handler für das-Ereignis auf die folgenden Eigenschaften zu:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-103">To obtain information related to an `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` event, access the following properties in the handler for the event:</span></span>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-104">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> -Eigenschaft verweist auf die Position des Eingabe Geräts im generierten Audiostream.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-104">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> property references the input device's position in its generated audio stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-105">Im Gegensatz dazu verweist <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> die-Eigenschaft auf die Position der Erkennung in der Audioeingabe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-105">By contrast, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> property references the recognizer's position within its audio input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-106">Diese Positionen können unterschiedlich sein.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-106">These positions can be different.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-107">Weitere Informationen finden Sie unter [Verwenden von sprach Erkennungs Ereignissen](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-107">For more information, see [Using Speech Recognition Events](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-108">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A> -Eigenschaft gibt an, welches Problem aufgetreten ist.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-108">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A> property indicates which problem occurred.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> wird von <xref:System.EventArgs> abgeleitet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="2ff0d-110">Im folgenden Beispiel wird ein Ereignishandler definiert, der Informationen zu <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioSignalProblemOccurred> einem Ereignis sammelt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2ff0d-110">The following example defines an event handler that gathers information about an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioSignalProblemOccurred> event.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.  
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the AudioSignalProblemOccurred event.  
  sre.AudioSignalProblemOccurred += new EventHandler<AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs>(sre_AudioSignalProblemOccurred);  
}  
  
// Gather information when the AudioSignalProblemOccurred event is raised.  
void sre_AudioSignalProblemOccurred(object sender, AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs e)  
{  
  StringBuilder details = new StringBuilder();  
  
  details.AppendLine("Audio signal problem information:");  
  details.AppendFormat(  
    " Audio level:               {0}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Audio position:            {1}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Audio signal problem:      {2}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Recognition engine audio position: {3}" + Environment.NewLine,  
    e.AudioLevel, e.AudioPosition,  e.AudioSignalProblem,  
    e.RecognizerAudioPosition);  
  
  // Insert additional event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
